Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of building indexes for large genomic databases, which involves data structures and algorithms for efficient text processing and indexing. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Data Mining (cs.DM), or Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories of arXiv CS. Specifically, cs.DS is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new preprocessing step for generating a parse of the input text, which is a fundamental problem in text processing and indexing. cs.IR is also likely as the paper discusses the use of the Burrows-Wheeler Transform (BWT) for building indexes, which is a popular technique in information retrieval. cs.CC, cs.DM, and cs.DB are less likely but still possible as the paper may involve computational complexity analysis, data mining techniques, and database management issues.
